{"questionId":"11740","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Paul wants to buy a car. He needs to take out a loan for $7000. The car salesman offers him a loan with an interest rate of 8%, compounded annually. Paul considers two options to repay the loan.</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Option 1: Pay $200 each month, until the loan is fully repaid</p>\n<p style=\"padding-left:180px;\">Option 2: Make 24 equal monthly payments.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Use option 2 to calculate</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the total amount that Paul has to pay.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"24 \\times 315.7 = {\\text{\\$}}7580{\\text{ }}\\left( {{\\text{\\$}}7576.80} \\right)\">\n  <mn>24</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>315.7</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>$</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mn>7580</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>$</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>7576.80</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11740","referenceCode":"EXM.2.SL.TZ0.1b.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the total amount that Paul has to pay.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.7—Loan repayments and amortization"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}